&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert Band 8a Post&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cardio-Respiratory Department at Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is looking to recruit an &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;enthusiastic and dedicated Highly Specialist Cardiac Physiologist to the post of Service Lead for Echocardiography and Non Invasive cardiac investigations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wirral University Teaching Hospital is developing services in a variety of areas within the department.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; The department currently delivers an extensive range of Cardiology investigations including Transthoracic Echocardiography, Transoesophageal Echocardiography, Dobutamine Stress Echocardiography, Tilt Testing, Exercise Tolerance Testing, Ambulatory ECG &amp; Blood Pressure Monitoring, Pacing implant and follow up and Catheter Lab procedures. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will have a BSc in Clinical Physiology or equivalent professional qualification with a minimum of three years clinical experience at Band 7.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BSE accreditation and professional registration are essential for this post along with proven knowledge, skills and experience in all aspects of Echocardiography.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical experience in other Non-Invasive diagnostic investigations would be an advantage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are required to have good organisational skills and excellent interpersonal skills which will be essential to work as part of a team in this busy developing department. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ontinuing professional development is encouraged and promoted within this department. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact Deborah Mills, Department Manager or Laura Stanton, Deputy Manager, on 0151 604 7380.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
